the junkie on this guy.

00:07.341 --> 00:09.308
That is such a leap, Jay.
You don't know that.

00:09.310 --> 00:12.177
- You've been busy. This is awesome.
- That petrograph...

00:12.179 --> 00:15.047
It's a drawing of
the constellation Gemini.

00:15.049 --> 00:17.516
From mythology,
like the peacock.

00:17.518 --> 00:19.018
Danny...
You don't need to say anything.

00:19.020 --> 00:20.285
When you're ready...

00:20.287 --> 00:22.287
Next week, next month,
next year...

00:22.289 --> 00:23.956
Just say the word.

00:23.958 --> 00:25.591
I don't think your
drawings cause the future.

00:25.593 --> 00:27.092
I think they predict it.

00:27.094 --> 00:28.527
So, I'm not making things happen.

00:28.529 --> 00:30.362
I just know about them first.

00:30.364 --> 00:33.232
Until we're sure the boy
is our Holy Grail,

00:33.234 --> 00:34.566
we sit tight.

00:36.437 --> 00:38.971
- Alice...
- You're going to save him.

00:42.410 --> 00:44.777
Heads up, everybody.
Here it comes.

00:47.448 --> 00:49.348
- They're gonna die!
- It's a calling.

00:49.350 --> 00:50.582
Griffin's blood work.

00:50.584 --> 00:52.284
He's got the same blood marker.

00:52.286 --> 00:53.685
Just like Zeke.

00:53.687 --> 00:55.754
So, if I'm saying that a bomb's
gonna go off...

00:55.756 --> 00:57.222
if I'm the only one
who knows where...

00:57.224 --> 00:58.524
Do you know where, Griffin?

00:58.526 --> 01:00.559
...then I'm the only one
who can save the day.

01:00.561 --> 01:04.530
Looks like I got myself
a get-out-of-jail-free card.

